                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/1076: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>U. S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">Indianapolis</hi>,”</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-02T22:00:00-06:00">July 2, 1933—10
                            p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. For Hull. Your 88, July 2, 8 p.m. Your Monday statement excellent and I think
                    my statement sent you 3 hours ago supplements <pb facs="0777" n="675"
                        xml:id="pg_675"/> and ties in with it very well. Let me know when you decide
                    on hours of release. Congratulations on the clear and dignified position you are
                    taking and my warm regards. The country is behind you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
